Warnołęka  () is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Nowe Warpno, within Police County, West Pomeranian Voivodeship, in northwestern Poland, close to the German border. It lies approximately  east of Nowe Warpno,  northwest of Police, and  northwest of the regional capital Szczecin.
